IoT-Based Smart Aquaponics System with TinyML Anomaly Detection and Automatic Fish Feeder
  Project Concept

This project develops an intelligent aquaponics system using:

IoT (ESP32) → Collects real-time data
Sensors → Monitor water and environment
TinyML (Machine Learning) → Detect anomalies
Actuators → Automatically control system
Auto Fish Feeder → Ensures regular feeding

  Components Used
🔹 Controller
ESP32
🔹 Sensors (Max 5)
pH Sensor
TDS Sensor
Water Temperature Sensor (DS18B20)
Water Level Sensor
DHT22 (Air temp + humidity)

  Actuators
Relay-controlled Water Pump
Automatic Fish Feeder (Servo Motor)
Buzzer / LED (Alert)
🔹 Software
Arduino IDE
Python (ML training)
TensorFlow Lite Micro

  Working Principle
Step 1 — Data Collection

ESP32 continuously reads:

pH
TDS
Temperature
Water level
Step 2 — Data Processing
  Basic Mode (Threshold)
  smart Mode(TinyMl)

  Step 3 -- Decision Making
Condition	Action
Low water	Turn ON pump
High TDS	Circulate water
High temperature	Cooling
Scheduled time	Activate fish feeder
Anomaly	Alert + action

  Machine Learning Flow
Step 1 — Data Collection
Collect sensor data into CSV
Step 2 — Training (Python)

Input:

[pH, TDS, Temp, WaterLevel]

Model:

Autoencoder / Neural Network
  
Step 3 — Conversion
Convert model → .tflite
Convert → C array
Step 4 — Deployment
Upload to ESP32
Real-time prediction
